    <summary>The message discusses the security risk associated with JSON-RPC and suggests that enabling it should require technical proficiency. Chris Evans proposes that Bitcoin.conf settings be editable within the app, rather than through an external editor. Additionally, he suggests that enabling RPC server mode should be easier. In a December 20, 2013 email chain, Wladimir responded to Chris Evans by recommending Diapolo's pull request to add options to the options dialog box. However, he cautioned against making it too easy to inadvertently change RPC settings and cause harm. The pull request did not include RPC settings. The message includes a PGP signature from the author.</summary>
